      <body>
         
         <head><emph>For Better or For Worse</emph>, <date when="2018-05-28">May 28, 2018</date></head><!-- The title of the comic is its date. So change the two dates in this line, keeping them both in the proper format -->
         
         <div type="panelGrp" xml:id="ForBetterorForWorse2018-05-28"><!-- Make sure that the value of this xml:id matches the idno from line 35 above. If there is a setting, weather, activities, or Bechdel test, tag them in the <div> with ana="" -->
            
            <cbml:panel n="1" ana="inside" characters="#JohnPatterson"><!-- In each of the four panel blocks, record the characters that appear in the panel.   -->
               <note resp="#r-IF" type="panelDesc">John slams the door as he enters the house.</note><!-- Put your r-name from the taxonomy (e.g., #r-HJ, #r-DM, #r-AL, #r-KS) as the value of the resp attribute. Give a quick description of what happens in this panel -->
               <sound>SLAM!</sound><!-- Put in the character who is speaking. If there are no speech bubbles, remove this line. If it's a different type of bubble than a speech bubble, change the @type value.-->
               <!-- Add a second (or third!) <cbml:balloon> if there are multiple speech bubbles in a panel -->
               <!-- In addition to <cbml:balloon>, you also have the choice of <cbml:caption> for text that is not in a speech balloon (this will probably be incredibly rare in our corpus), <sound>, <figure> for music, or <floatingText type="diegetic">. -->
               <docDate>05-28</docDate><!-- Include the date as written in the comic. Move to a different panel if needed. Move it above the signature if need be. Isebelle - DATE IS BETWEEN PANELS 1 AND 2! NOT SURE HOW TO SHOW THIS! -->
            </cbml:panel>
            
            <cbml:panel n="2" ana="inside" characters="#EllyPatterson"><!-- In panels 2, 3, and 4, also record the transition type according to McCloud using the tr- value from the taxonomy -->
               <note resp="#r-IF" type="panelDesc">John slams more things around. This startles Elly, who is making a peanut butter and jelly sandwich.</note>
               <sound>SLAM! WHAM! BANG!</sound>
            </cbml:panel>
            
            <cbml:panel n="3" ana="inside" characters="#EllyPatterson">
               <note resp="#r-IF" type="panelDesc">Elly watches as John slams the door, again, on his way outside.</note>
               <sound>SLAM!</sound>
            </cbml:panel>
            
            <cbml:panel n="4" ana="outside" characters="#JohnPatterson #EllyPatterson">
               <note resp="#r-IF" type="panelDesc">Elly sticks her head out the front door to shout after John, who is looking very grumpy as he walks away.</note>
               <cbml:balloon type="speech" who="#EllyPatterson">A LITTLE TESTY THIS MORNING, ARE WE?!!</cbml:balloon>
               <docAuthor>Lynn</docAuthor><!-- Include signature. If rendered differently, encode with a <hi rend=""> element. Move this to a different panel if need be. -->
            </cbml:panel>
            
         </div>
